    "where ∥X j ∥ 2 is the l 2 norm of X[:, j].",
    "They consider an output index i and construct the sets of all weights connecting into i: {W uv | u = i}.",
    "Finally, they remove all the lowest s% connections in each group where s% is the target sparsity.",
    "Sharma et al. (2023) introduced LAyer-SElective Rank reduction (LASER) and observed performance gains across multiple reasoning tasks, including TruthfulQA (Beeching et al., 2023) and the Bias in Bios dataset (De-Arteaga et al., 2019).",
